#T_SP=webanno.custom.Referent|entity|infstat
#T_RL=webanno.custom.Coref|type|BT_webanno.custom.Referent
#Text=To me ... London ... the coverage on TV in Britain , but also here , some countries are ahead of others , but basically it 's being treated like the Olympics .
#Text=Yeah !
#Text=Yeah .
#Text=There was n't a lot of difference between .
#Text=Huge crowds ...
#Text=Huge crowds !
#Text=We played for our silver medal in a sell-out crowd ... you could n't see a vacant seat around the place .
#Text=I was looking around the North Greenwich Arena ...
#Text=And that arena !
#Text=The seats went up and up and up !
#Text=And as it was filling on the night , you could see that even that top deck had people sitting in it .
#Text=I guess in 2000 even , to fill stadiums , which we did , we gave APC and school programs , a lot of school kids came to fill seats and things .
#Text=We did n't necessarily see that in London .
#Text=They were paid seats !
#Text=People had gone out and spent money on tickets to come and see that sport .
#Text=I saw school groups at the football and the goalball , but not at the basketball .
#Text=No.
#Text=Which is a big difference also , that people are willing to come and pay to watch that level of sport .
#Text=I was very impressed with the standard of play .
#Text=The standard , over the years , has improved so much .
#Text=But the good thing is , we 're looking at development .
#Text=So we 've got the next rung of girls , and guys , coming through the group .
#Text=Like , we 've got girls that were n't necessarily up to selection for London but will probably be right up there for Rio ...
#Text=Our squad will open , come January , for the first training camp .

#Text=That will be an invitational to most of the girls who are playing women 's league and those sorts of things , and from there they 'll do testing and stuff , cutting down and they 'll select a side for Osaka for February , but the program will remain open leading into the next world championship , which is in Canada .
#Text=What 's in Osaka ?
#Text=The Osaka Cup .
#Text=It 's held every year in February , so that will be the Gliders ' first major tournament ...
#Text=After the Paralympics .
#Text=Yeah .
#Text=So everyone 's taking an opportunity now to have a bit of a break .
#Text=And then after that ?
#Text=It 's the world championships in 2014 in Canada .
#Text=So that will be what they 're next training to .
#Text=How many tournaments do they normally play each year ?
#Text=We 've played a few .
#Text=And you often play more in a Paralympic year , because you 're looking to see the competition , and the other teams , and those sorts of things , so ...
#Text=This year we did Osaka , which Canada went to , China went to ... Japan , and us .
#Text=We then went to — and we 'd previously just been to Korea last November for qualification .
#Text=We 've been over to Germany .
#Text=We 've been to Manchester .
#Text=So we 've had a few tournaments where we 've travelled .
#Text=And then we 've had of course a tournament in Sydney about three weeks before we went to London .
#Text=And then of course we went to the Netherlands , before we went on to Cardiff in Wales .
